column24: I regret to say that I answered the question as if you were asking about today specifically, as a prelude perhaps to making ratings of individuals featured in photographs with little other information, rather than about people in general across time - like "What kind of person is this, and what kind of life had they had?"  So I was thinking of specific experiences, but rated lower than I would have otherwise to be more reflective of my general world view.  I attempted to reload the study to start again once I saw the second question (10 years), but that brought up the same page without restarting the study from the beginning as I had hoped.  Still, my initial response was honest, so I had no choice but to modify my subsequent responses to be more reflective of the initial rating, if also less grave.  I might not have rated people today as less than 20 years ago, or even 10 years ago, but I will say that what we are seeing now is a polarization and enmity that has brought into focus ill currents that have been running through society unresolved and largely untended for a long time through the history of this country, while the world becomes more challenged by a diversity of issues, and the issue of diversity among people as well.  People are threatened, also more impatient with the perceived lack of progress.  I hope that helps, in view of the likely distortion of the ratings I made.
